Assignment1.01, I am using a queue implementation with seeding to generate terrain as professor shaeffer mentioned during class, I have 7 seeds that generate on random spots on the map and grow using the queue, and 
the buildings always generate on opposite sides of the road. Buildings are SUPPOSED to generate on mountains or water, because I thought it was cool. Same goes for roads, I thought it was cool to have roads going through/over 
mountains and water. my queue implementation does have some unused functions, but I kept them just in case I need them later. While my main file has no functions, I plan to make the code easier to read and have more functions
in future assignments.
